The paper proposes a neural model for multi-passage machine reading comprehension, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). The model also involves cross-passage answer verification, which can be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
